The paper deals with polar codes, which are a type of error correction codes used in communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses decoding techniques, which falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of multiple polarizing matrices and the optimization of decoding schedules involve optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses efficient implementations, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
